      "title": "Sri Lanka shares marginally up in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s shares moved up marginally in the mid-morning trade after slipping in two consecutive sessions, Colombo Stock Exchange data showed.",
        "The main All Share Price Index moved up 0.08 percent or 6.37 points to 7, 645 at 1130 hours.",
        "The most liquid index S&P SL 20 gained 0.04 percent or 0.96 points to 2,435.24.",
        "Top gainers were Aitken Spence, Hatton National Bank and Hayleys Fabric. (Colombo/Jul26/2022)"
